rComments: best prof ever. so helpful, so clear, so caring, she's worth the tuition trust me!!

This is a difficult course so just going to lectures won't cut it. However, help is available everywhere- you just need to ask for it. Do not skip ahead if you not intimately sure how the previous topic works. Ask for help in that case- it's surprising how it bites you in the ass if you skip ahead without thoroughly understanding the previous mate.

Gives very clear explanation of all topics. If you are taking 3 hour long classes, be prepared to write non stop for most of that time. I took a course with her during the summer semester, and I finished a 200 pg notebook in 1.5 months. Overall a great lecturer!!!
